fencesitters key for joseph lhota  crains new york business login register contact us subscribe september    am fencesitters key for joseph lhota its decision time for donors hesitant to embrace the republican nominee by chris bragg comments email print × photo andrew hawkins republican mayoral nominee joseph lhota will face off against democratic candidate bill de blasio in the november election this week in crains september   listen to the podcast or download last december when joseph lhota resigned as chairman of the metropolitan transit authority to launch a mayoral bid many business leaders indicated theyd take a waitandsee approach to his underdog candidacy in a city that is heavily democratic at a minimum the business community will be hedging its bets explained kathryn wylde president and ceo of the partnership for new york city an organization of the citys largest private employers it is still likely that the person who comes out of the democratic primary will be the mayor at the time city council speaker christine quinn was perceived as mayor michael bloombergs businessfriendly successor but in last weeks democratic primary ms quinn placed a distant third while the most liberal contender public advocate bill de blasio outpaced the field former city comptroller bill thompson who like ms quinn is perceived as businessfriendly finished a distant second and may not even qualify for a runoff with mr de blasio article continues below advertisement the results raise the question of whether the business community will move behind mr lhota despite his odds in a city with six democrats for every republican mr lhota had raised a total of  million as of late august compared with mr de blasios  million but mr de blasios taxandspend pledges may change that the real estate industry and others in new york have to be noticing bill de blasios rhetoric said republican consultant bill oreilly theres no going back to the center from where he is friends supply funds so far business interests have wagered more on mr de blasio whose major campaign contributors such as the real estate and taxi industries have financial stakes in city policy mr lhotas biggest fundraisers have been former giuliani administration colleagues of the  bundlers who have raised more than  for him six worked in the administration with mr lhota who was deputy mayor and budget director many of them retain ties to city government mr lhotas biggest campaign bundler is robert harding an attorney who has raised more than  much of it from his politically prominent law firm greenberg traurig mr harding is the son of the late liberal party head raymond harding who had extremely close ties with mr giuliani and later pleaded guilty to securities violations in  the sons appointment as mr giulianis budget director in  raised eyebrows because he had little experience managing fiscal matters other major lhota bundlers from the giuliani world include former deputy mayor randy mastro a politically connected attorney who in classic bethedging style was also a major bundler for the democratic mr thompson agostino cangemi an assistant counsel in the giuliani administration who is now a lobbyist john odermatt a former commissioner of the office of emergency management and now a managing director at citigroup and john mascialino a former official in the department of citywide administrative services and an attorney who now heads greenberg traurigs government and law policy practice mr lhotas postgiuliani stint as an executive vice president of cablevision is also proving helpful in his run for mayor the companys president and ceo james dolan has raised more than  while richard hochman a business consultant who is mr lhotas secondbiggest fundraiser has served on cablevisions board of directors mr hochman said he does not have business before the city that would benefit from a lhota administration he gave to mr lhota he added because of their personal relationship and because he believes the candidate would preserve the gains of the bloomberg and giuliani eras i grew up in this city mr hochman said i saw it in  i saw it in the s and for the past  years giuliani and bloomberg made it such a better place to live i dont want to go back given mr de blasios momentum mr lhota must reach beyond his inner circle perhaps even to disaffected supporters of mr de blasios vanquished democratic rivals during the republican primary billionaire opponent john catsimatidis repeatedly said that mr lhota could not compete in november because of a lack of resources mr bloomberg running as a republican and independent spent more than  million to eke out a third term in  billionaire steps up mr lhota is getting help from an outside group called new yorkers for proven leadership which was started by three former giuliani aides it has already received  from billionaire david koch and his wife and is launching a national fundraising effort touting mr lhota as a moderate republican who can win in a deepblue city like mr lhotas campaign the committee might struggle to get enough donations to make a major impact as new york republicans have in recent statewide elections but a spokesman for the group michael mckeon said he believed business supporters of ms quinn and mr thompson would now flock to mr lhota i think people who supported the other candidates are now going to take a harder look at a guy who is the most liberal candidate and the farthest to the left said mr mckeon theyre going to take a hard look at de blasio and theyre going to take a second look at joe that will be an uphill fight as the vanquished democrats have all pledged to support their partys nominee a number of democrats crossed party lines to support mr bloomberg in his  and  reelection campaigns but mr lhota lacks several advantages that the mayor had incumbency weak competition and an unlimited campaign budget mr lhotas thirdlargest fundraiser joseph dussich of jad corp of america stands out as the rare businessowning lhota bundler whose company might benefit from a lhota mayoralty mr dussich a queens building maintenance supplies dealer who had raised more than  through july received a visit from mr lhota in august during a tour of small businesses mr lhota touted the mintscented trash bags sold by mr dussich that can repel mice raccoons and other critters during the visit mr dussich who did not return a request for comment lamented that the parks department was rebuffing his efforts to sell the trash bags to the city mr lhota called it the type of product that could keep manufacturing jobs in the city of course you can if you put your mind to it mr lhota said according to the new york times but youve got to think about what the products are that new yorkers need a version of this article appears in the september   print issue of crains new york business greenberg traurigpartnership for new york citybill de blasiobill thompsonchristine quinnjames dolanjohn catsimatidisjoseph lhotakathryn wyldemichael bloombergraymond hardingpoliticstop storiesqueens get crains morning insider sign up for the morning insider email and receive political news and musings every morning at  am more newsletters › advertisement comments crains recommends from around the web business lists  book of lists minorityowned businesses womenowned businesses top manhattan office leases health pulse  compensation database resources executive moves events calendar data center for the record get crains morning insider sign up for the morning insider email and receive political news and musings every morning at  am more newsletters › latest most popular latest beef recall  dolan cant sell msg networks infecting a patient with hepatitis c to save  shunning solar power could make new york as layoffs hit vice petsitting in nyc is illegal but animal most popular jetblue plans to build a new terminal at jfk the russian whose lawyer met with donald david greenfield will leave city council to cuomo campaign exploits loophole to get rent streeteasys rental listings drop by half related news catsimatidis mailer attacks fellow republican thompson concedes democrats unify behind de blasio candidates condemn real estate spending even on their behalf bill de blasio parttime populist fraud drained peninsula hospital suit says why money message woes may doom lhota amid subway crisis cuomo taps an old hand to head mta  the new york times nytimescom no longer supports internet explorer  or earlier please upgrade your browser learn more » sections home search skip to content skip to navigation view mobile version the new york times ny  regionamid subway crisis cuomo taps an old hand to head mta search subscribe now log in  settings close search httpsnytimstqpvxf advertisement supported by ny  region amid subway crisis cuomo taps an old hand to head mta by emma g fitzsimmons and jesse mckinleyjune   continue reading the main story share this page continue reading the main story photo gov andrew m cuomo speaking last month about mass transit he has proposed legislation to add two new members to the authority’s board whom he would select credit hiroko masuikethe new york times joseph j lhota who led the metropolitan transportation authority under gov andrew m cuomo before leaving for a failed mayoral run in  has been chosen by the governor to return as chairmanthe surprise afterhours announcement was approved late on wednesday by the state senate after its finance committee voiced its support at an impromptu meeting in the capitol during which mr lhota — speaking over skype — expressed his frustration with problems with the city’s subways“i know the mta can do a lot better” he saidas new yorkers reach a breaking point over the constant subway delays governor cuomo has moved this week to strengthen his grip on the transportation authority which runs the city’s transit systembut there is a catch mr cuomo already controls the agency and has been calling the shots there for some time advertisement continue reading the main story mr lhota’s nomination came just hours after the authority’s monthly board meeting in lower manhattan in which several members pushed back against mr cuomo’s power grab he had proposed legislation on tuesday to add two new members to the authority’s board whom he would select continue reading the main story advertisement continue reading the main story board members urged mr cuomo to focus on more pressing issues including releasing a comprehensive plan to fix the creaky subway system and securing funding for the improvementsthe board had been “neutered” by mr cuomo’s growing influence said veronica vanterpool a member who had been recommended by mayor bill de blasio many of the authority’s announcements come from the governor’s office she said and his preferences were prioritized in the fiveyear capital planinstead of an increase in the governor’s power the board needs independence ms vanterpool said“we need to ensure the decisions we’re making are on behalf of the public that we serve and not caught up in this political process that we’re often hampered by” ms vanterpool saidjames e vitiello a board member from dutchess county said he did not understand why mr cuomo was suddenly trying to change the board’s structure when he had dallied for so long — nearly five months — in naming a permanent leader to run the agency photo transit activists in brooklyn in january mr cuomo proposed adding two new members to the mta board but some board members say that naming a chairman for the authority and working harder for subway improvements are more important credit nicole bengivenothe new york times “that just makes no sense to me” mr vitiello saidwith the last scheduled day of the legislative session in albany dragging past dark on wednesday it was unclear if mr cuomo’s legislation might pass or if another bill to split the roles of chairman and chief executive into two jobs might the governor’s father gov mario m cuomo similarly sought to add members to the board in  to gain a majority but he backed down after mayor edward i koch and suburban officials rose up in oppositionscott rechler a new board member appointed by the governor defended mr cuomo’s legislation mr rechler said the governor wanted to take full responsibility for the agency — and its challenges “let him put  percent of his political capital his expertise his energy his relationships into fixing something that is immensely broken” he said newsletter sign up continue reading the main story please verify youre not a robot by clicking the box invalid email address please reenter you must select a newsletter to subscribe to sign up you agree to receive occasional updates and special offers for the new york timess products and services thank you for subscribing an error has occurred please try again later you are already subscribed to this email view all new york times newsletters see sample manage email preferences not you privacy policy opt out or contact us anytime still mr cuomo has already exerted a great deal of influence over the authority he took an active role in the completion of the second avenue subway and presided over its lavish opening he has pressed for electronic tolling at bridges and tunnels and a project to add a track on the long island rail roadbut only recently has he started focusing to a significant degree on the dismal performance of the subway system as riders have begun to accuse the governor of ignoring their plight advertisement continue reading the main story the authority’s last chairman and chief executive thomas f prendergast stepped down in january the agency’s interim executive director veronique hakim interviewed for the top job but mr cuomo’s office apparently opted to go with a proven asset in mr lhota it was not clear if mr cuomo still intended to create a separate position of chief executive and if so if ms hakim would be considered for itms vanterpool said board members were often left out of key decisions including the long island rail road’s recent move to offer discounts to riders who are diverted during repairs at pennsylvania station in new york this summer the railroad announced the discounts on tuesday a day after mr cuomo called for them in a speechpolly trottenberg the city’s transportation commissioner and a board member offered another example of a time when the board was not consulted when mr cuomo announced the hiring of a new chief development officer for the authority in april ms trottenberg said she learned about the news when she read it in the new york timeson wednesday ms trottenberg said that the governor had already been “handson” at the authority and that the city and the mayor also wanted to have a voice in the transit system she declined to comment on the governor’s push to add two board members but she had urged mr cuomo to pick a leader for the authority hours later the governor chose mr lhota who said he wanted to hire an executive director to run the agency on a daily basis“there’s a lot of basic work we have to get done” he said continue reading the main story we’re interested in your feedback on this page tell us what you think related coverage with mta in need of a boss cuomo may finally pick one or two june   related coverage with mta in need of a boss cuomo may finally pick one or two june   whats next loading go to home page » site index the new york times joe lhota  wikipedia joe lhota from wikipedia the free encyclopedia   redirected from joseph j lhota jump to navigation search a major contributor to this article appears to have a close connection with its subject it may require cleanup to comply with wikipedias content policies particularly neutral point of view please discuss further on the talk page february  learn how and when to remove this template message joe lhota chairman and ceo of the mta incumbent assumed office june   governor andrew cuomo preceded by fernando ferrer acting in office january   – december   governor andrew cuomo preceded by jay walder succeeded by fernando ferrer acting personal details born joseph j lhota  october   age  the bronx new york us political party republican education georgetown university harvard business school known for republican nominee for new york city mayor  website nyu langone medical center biography official twitter joseph j lhota ˈloʊtə born october   is an american public servant and a former politician he served as the chairman of the metropolitan transportation authority and was also a former deputy mayor of new york city he was the republican nominee in an unsuccessful bid for the  election for mayor of new york city in january  he became senior vice president vice dean and chief of staff at nyu langone medical center in  he returned to the chairmanship of the mta but will not run the authority daytoday contents  early life and education  private sector career  public service career  giuliani administration  chairman of the metropolitan transportation authority  mayoral candidacy  return to mta  personal life  political beliefs  references  external links early life and educationedit joe lhota was born in the bronx new york the son of jackie and joseph joe lhota a new york city police officer his paternal grandfather was a new york city firefighter and his maternal grandfather was a new york city taxi driver his father’s family is czech his maternal grandfather was of italian descent and his maternal grandmother was jewish lhota was raised catholic and selfidentifies as a christian although he is considered jewish according to jewish law the family later moved to lindenhurst he was the first member of his family to attend college graduating with honors from georgetown universitys mcdonough school of business with a degree in business administration in  he received an mba degree from harvard business school in  private sector careeredit upon graduating from georgetown university lhota joined arthur andersen  co in washington dc and specialized in health care finance he worked there for two years before entering the harvard business school following harvard lhota returned to new york city and began a fourteenyear career as an investment banker at first boston and paine webber he specialized in public finance serving state and local governments throughout the united states in  lhota became executive vice president of cablevision as well as president of lightpath a fiberbased telecommunications company that offered telephone and high speed data services to businesses throughout the new york area in  he joined the madison square garden company as executive vice president as a member of the senior management team and chief administrative officer joseph lhota in january  in early  after his mayoral run lhota was appointed as senior vice president vice dean and chief of staff at nyu langone medical center in charge of government outreach emergency preparedness and business planning from  to  lhota served as a member of the board of directors of first aviation services inc in  favs became a private company in  lhota became a board member of cablevision systems corporation and was chairman of its audit committee until the company was sold in june  to altice usa in  lhota became an independent member of the board of directors and chairman of the audit committee of msg networks public service careeredit giuliani administrationedit in  lhota joined the administration of mayor rudy giuliani where he held several positions over giulianis two terms he first served as chief of staff to the deputy mayor for finance and economic development and that year was quickly promoted to new york city finance commissioner in  he was selected as director of the office of management and budget in  giuliani appointed lhota to deputy mayor for operations as the head of the mayors rat abatement task force he was humorously known as the rat czar lhota served as mayor giulianis liaison to the white house united states congress governor of new york new york state legislature and new york city council additionally he was responsible for oversight of the city’s relationships with the public employee unions and development of collective bargaining agreement strategies chairman of the metropolitan transportation authorityedit on october   new york state governor andrew cuomo nominated lhota to serve as chairman of the metropolitan transportation authority the largest mass transit provider in the united states servicing  million customers daily while awaiting confirmation by the new york state senate lhota began serving as interim ceo he was unanimously confirmed on january   mta chair joe lhota speaks with transit workers during sandy recovery efforts at brooklyns atlantic terminal lhota giving a press briefing at the hugh l carey tunnel with governor cuomo and albany leaders lhota was responsible for new york city transit’s fastrack program which saw more than  million in productivity gains in  by concentrating and targeting subway station maintenance efforts in july  lhota announced a  million service enhancement package that restored transportation services that the mta had previously eliminated in  and added new transit services in underserved areas including williamsburg the south bronx and brooklyn navy yard—all new york city neighborhoods that had seen significant residential and commercial development since  lhota headed efforts to make information about the mta and its services more accessible to its customers through its website and apps he granted pay raises to managers at the mta when hurricane sandy devastated much of the new york metropolitan area in october  lhota shut down the mta in advance of the storm and moved the systems trains to high ground to avoid damage from the storm surge his other notable hurricane recovery measure was the rapid deployment of a free rockaway park shuttle to service the worst damaged line in rockaway queens lhota also directed the mta to provide regular details and updates to the public on the recovery efforts via social media and local news channels in january  governor cuomo appointed lhota to the committee charged with conducting a nationwide search for a new chair and chief executive officer of the mta mayoral candidacyedit october   lhota preparing to march at a school choice rally across the brooklyn bridge along with over  parents from lowincome neighborhoods who have children in publicly colocated charter schools lhotas campaign outreaches to new york citys indian immigrant community main article new york city mayoral election  lhota resigned as head of the mta on december   to explore running for mayor of new york city on january   he filed paperwork with the new york city board of elections and the new york state board of elections to formally launch his mayoral campaign lhota won the endorsements of all three major daily new york city newspapers for the republican primary with the new york times stating few people know better than mr lhota how city government works he won the primary on september   with  of the vote defeating john catsimatidis who garnered  and george t mcdonald who captured  in the general election campaign lhota received the endorsements of crains new york business am new york newsday the jewish voice and the new york post lhotas economic plan focused on job creation primarily through municipal tax cuts he said he wanted to lower the general corporation tax phase out the commercial rent tax reform the unincorporated business tax and lower the hotel tax he proposed to cut the hotel occupancy tax to  from  and to lower property taxes lhota also proposed a tax incentive program to allow private sector developers to build mixeduse housing to incorporate affordable units he planned to improve education in new york city by doubling the number of public charter schools particularly in lowincome neighborhoods he participated in a school choice rally organized by success academy charter schools to protest democratic candidate bill de blasios proposed rent requirement for the citys charter schools that were operating in public school buildings and ban on further colocation in public school buildings he also proposed universal prekindergarten without raising taxescitation needed lhota lost the general election to de blasio garnering  votes or  of the voter turnout return to mtaedit in june  lhota was nominated by cuomo to return to chairman of the mta lhota will remain at nyu langone as he will not be the daytoday executive of the mta that being veronique hakim personal lifeedit lhota is married to tamra roberts lhota the couple met while she was working in washington dc they have one child while he was raised catholic and identifies as christian lhotas maternal grandmother was jewish when asked why he didnt capitalize on his religious heritage to garner the citys jewish voters he responded i think that would be patronizing political beliefsedit lhota defended his support for prochoice and samesex marriage as not only being in sync with new york citys socially liberal outlook but consistent with jeffersonian republicanism or democracy and its intellectual premise in classical liberalism his accommodation of fiscal conservatism and socially progressive views were criticized by some local social conservative groups while independents applauded his position as an example of thirdway politics lhota called for expulsion of donald trump from the republican party after trumps remarks about banning muslims from entering the united states referencesedit  a b kornbluh jacob may   exclusive joe ‘yoely’ lhota on his relationship with the jews the jewish press retrieved september     zak irina september   the players  an election round up jewish voice new york ny   dawsey josh nyu langone hires joe lhota retrieved february     a b watch out subway cats joe lhota is running the mta again retrieved june     a b cuomo nominates lhota to chair mta but not run